Class Variable

  • java.lang.Object
    • parser.Variable

  • public class Variable
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a variable It is used to know if a variable is a terminal or not and contains some useful methods

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      Variable(LexicalVariable variable)
      The constructor that takes only a variable, that means the variable is not a terminal
      Variable(LexicalVariable variable, java.lang.Object value)
      The constructor that will set the variable and the value of the variable If this constructor is called, it means that the variable has a value and therefore is a terminal
      Variable(java.lang.String terminal)
      This constructor takes a string that represents a terminal in the form "variable: value
